        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p>To the Reader</p>
            <p>The events of the life of this Great Man have arising separately<lb/> with the events
                in the chains of wisdom and learning which<lb/> have gone forth &amp; been exchanged
                (spread abroad) in the march of<lb/> the last seventy years. For all his works &amp;
                deeds in which<lb/> he laboured &amp; toiled all the days of his (fleeting) life,
                there are<lb/> weaved in &amp; intertwined in the midst of these new
                intelli=<lb/>gencies. And who is the man who has watched over (gives<lb/> attention)
                [the opening of] the gates of wisdom to see the wonders &amp; doings which<lb/>
                these latter days have brought forth upon us &amp; whose lips<lb/> have not chaunted
                    <del>the</del>
                <sic>praize</sic> whilst reaching out this great<lb/> one.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Wherefore I have brought forth from my heart (<hi rend="underline"
                    >al</hi>-<lb/><hi rend="underline">ready</hi> prepared <hi rend="underline">for
                    it</hi>) to narrate also to the sons of our<lb/> people who long to hear words
                in the Hebrew Tongue, the<lb/> genealogy of this beloved person, so that they
                may<lb/> warm up their hearts over the glory honor of the many (kinds<lb/> of)
                knowledge which have been spread over the Earth<lb/> in these our days; and to see
                in them the labors and<lb/> mighty <add>והשפלות</add> which have wearied, but not
                exhausted by<lb/> them their researches all their fleeting days to disclose the<lb/>
                hidden places of wisdom, and to bring forth the truth for its own<lb/> sake. And
                also, in order to raise up establish in this way a memo-<lb/>rial to this wise name
                in the <add>?</add> of the Hebrew Language</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>an additional <hi rend="underline">binding</hi>
                <del>which will adorn</del> his great wisdom, <add>עמד צרוך</add> his justice<lb/>
                and righteousness to the happiness <add>?</add> the children of
                    <placeName>Israel</placeName>.<lb/> Speaking well of them before all peoples
                &amp; tongues. And<lb/> every Israelite who loves his people will rejoice in
                his<lb/> heart, will fill his mouth with praise &amp; thanksgiving to the<lb/> honor
                of this beloved wise man, whose name shall<lb/> flourish as long as the sun remains
                and his righteousness<lb/> will stand forever.</p>
            <p><placeName>Berlin</placeName>
                <date>September 1857</date>.</p>
            <p>
